## Step 5.5: Write Build Handoff

Write `TASK_DIR/handoff-build.json` summarizing the build outcome:
```json
{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "source_phase": "build",
  "target_phase": "eval",
  "task_id": "task-NNN",
  "summary": "<what was built, CI result, key decisions made during implementation>",
  "decisions": [{"what": "...", "why": "...", "classification": "mechanical|taste"}],
  "risks": [{"description": "...", "mitigation": "...", "severity": "low|medium|high"}],
  "open_items": [{"description": "...", "owner": "evaluator|builder", "priority": "..."}],
  "artifacts_produced": ["build-rN.log", "<list of new/modified source files>"],
  "scope_changes": ["<any deviations from the plan, or empty>"],
  "created_at": "<ISO 8601 UTC>"
}
```

Then update `workflow-state.json` → `artifacts.handoff` to `"handoff-build.json"`.
If `workflow-state.json` does not exist, skip the update.

## Step 6: Commit

Stage and commit the implementation:

```bash
git add <specific-files-changed>
git commit -m "<type>(scope): implement task-NNN deliverables

Deliverables: (list what was implemented)
CI: all tests pass"
```

Use specific file paths — never `git add -A` or `git add .` to avoid including
unrelated changes.
